-- Baccarat, Neurones, PPR, Thermocompact May Move: French Equity Preview
-- B y   M a t t h e w   C a m p b e l l   a n d   J u l i e   C r u z
-- 2010-09-23T06:46:52Z
-- http://www.bloomberg.com/news/2010-09-23/baccarat-micropole-securidev-and-thermocompact-french-equity-preview.html
The following is a list of
companies whose shares may have unusual price changes in Paris.
Stock symbols are in parentheses after company names and prices
are from the last close.  France’s CAC 40 Index fell 1.3 percent to 3,735.05 in
Paris. The  SBF 120 Index  also lost 1.3 percent.  Baccarat  (BCRA FP): The crystal manufacturer narrowed its
first-half net loss to 611,000 euros ($819,000) from nearly 7
million euros last year. The shares gained 3.5 percent to 167.60
euros.  Compagnie Generale de Geophysique-Veritas  (GA FP): The
provider of geophysical services was downgraded to “neutral”
from “overweight” at JPMorgan Chase & Co. The shares slid 3.4
percent to 16.56 euros.  Technip SA  (TEC FP): Europe’s second-largest oilfield-
services was raised to “overweight” from “neutral” at the
brokerage. The shares added 0.4 percent to 57.64 euros.  Faurecia SA  (EO FP): Europe’s largest maker of car
interiors was rated “buy” in new coverage at UBS AG. The
shares slipped 0.5 percent to 16.44 euros.  Micropole  (MUN FP): The Internet consulting company
reported first-half net income of 1.3 million euros, little
changed from year-earlier levels, and said second-half forecasts
were “satisfactory.” The shares added 1.9 percent to 1.05
euros.  Neurones  (NRO FP): The computer-services company raised its
full-year revenue and operating margin forecasts after first-
half net profit climbed to 5.1 million euros from 4.9 million
euros a year earlier. The shares rose 1 percent to 7.16 euros.  PPR SA  (PP FP): The owner of the Bottega Veneta and Fnac
retail chains was cut to “neutral” from “buy” at Nomura
Holdings Inc. The shares fell 2 percent to 115.90 euros.  Securidev SA  (SCDV FP): The maker of conventional and
electronic locks returned to profit in the first half of the
year with net income of 4.3 million euros and maintained its
full-year forecast. The shares added 0.9 percent to 21.20 euros.  Thermocompact SA  (THER FP): The supplier of cable coatings
for the electronics industry posted a 2.36 million euro first-
half profit, up from an 883,000-euro loss last year. The shares
advanced 1.2 percent to 13.71 euros.  Vet’Affaires  (VET FP): The French discount-clothing
retailer returned to profit in the first half and forecast full-
year revenue of more than 100 million euros. The shares gained
1.3 percent to 23 euros.  To contact the reporters on this story:
